          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <placeName>New York</placeName>
                                        <date>13<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Jany 1854. 5614</date>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <placeName>239 Tenth Street</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">My dear sir,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">Having relinquished my clerical ap-<lb/>pointment
                                        in <placeName>Jamaica</placeName>, I have come hither for
                                        the purpose<lb/> of engaging my services in the
                                                  <placeName>U. S.</placeName> in the same
                                        sacred<lb/> calling. I possess Testimonials of the highest
                                        nature as a<lb/> Hazan, Preacher and Teacher. Previous to my
                                        departure I<lb/> had the additional satisfaction of
                                        receiving Two Public<lb/> addresses, one emanating from my
                                        former congr. of Spanish<lb/> Town, and the other from the
                                        entire Jewish Community of<lb/>
                                        <placeName>Kingston</placeName>. A copy of the latter I now
                                        enclose, and may I<lb/> request the kind insertion of the
                                        same in the “Occident” together<lb/> with any remarks which
                                        may prove serviceable to me in<lb/> this country. For this
                                        act I will feel grateful particularly<lb/> as I am a
                                        candidate for the vacant office of Minister of<lb/> the
                                        Portuguese Kahal of <placeName>Richmond Va</placeName>. The
                                                  <persName>Revd. Mr Isaacs</persName><lb/> has
                                        promised to use his influence for me in that quarter,<lb/>
                                        and if it would not be taxing your friendship too much,<lb/>
                                        a letter from you to any influential party there would
                                        be<lb/> material in forwarding my views.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">With God's blessing I will call to see<lb/> you
                                        shortly as I have much to say to you. The Occident<lb/> is
                                        scarcely seen in <placeName>Jamaica</placeName>, and were it
                                        not for the</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>kindness of <persName>Mr Delevante</persName>, who occasionally
                                        lent me<lb/> a no. I should have been in a similar
                                        plight.<lb/> Possibly I may suggest some method of promoting
                                        a<lb/> better circulation of so excellent a Mag. In
                                                  <placeName>Kingston</placeName>. I<lb/> paid
                                                  <persName>Miss S. C. Peixotto</persName> $3.25 for
                                        my subscription for one<lb/> year; since the period which
                                        this embraces I do not think<lb/> I have received six nos.
                                        However we will converse<lb/> further on the subject.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">With my best respects</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">Believe me</p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">Yours faithfully</p>
                              <p rend="indent(4)"><persName role="author">Henry S.
                                        Jacobs</persName>.</p>
                              <p>In your remarks, would you notify<lb/> that I am a Pupil of the
                                                  <persName>Revd. Isaac Lopez</persName><lb/> and
                                        have from him a Certificate of Efficiency<lb/> as a <hi
                                                  rend="underline">Portuguese</hi> Reader?</p>
                              <p rend="indent(6)">
                                        <date>1-13-1854C</date>
                              </p>
                              <pb n="3"/>
                              <p>Prepaid</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">
                                        <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p>pmail</p>
